## Objective

Update `useInteractiveShortcuts` to allow ArrowUp/ArrowDown to navigate options even when a textarea is focused. Currently, the `isTextInput` guard blocks all keyboard shortcuts except Enter/Escape when focus is on a textarea or input element. Users use Shift+Enter for newlines in the "Other" textarea.

## Current Code

In `apps/client/src/layers/shared/model/use-interactive-shortcuts.ts`, lines ~67-75:

```typescript
// In text input, only Enter/Esc work
if (isTextInput) {
  if (e.key === 'Enter' && !e.shiftKey) {
    e.preventDefault();
    onSubmit?.();
  }
  return;
}
```

## New Code

Replace the `isTextInput` block in the `question` branch with:

```typescript
if (isTextInput) {
  if (e.key === 'Enter' && !e.shiftKey) {
    e.preventDefault();
    onSubmit?.();
    return;
  }
  if (e.key === 'ArrowUp') {
    e.preventDefault();
    onNavigateOption?.('up');
    return;
  }
  if (e.key === 'ArrowDown') {
    e.preventDefault();
    onNavigateOption?.('down');
    return;
  }
  // Block digits and space in text input (let them type normally)
  return;
}
```

This allows:
- **ArrowUp/ArrowDown**: Navigate options (even from textarea)
- **Enter** (without Shift): Submit/advance
- **Shift+Enter**: Normal newline in textarea (not intercepted)
- **Digits, Space, other keys**: Type normally in textarea (not intercepted)

