## New Code

Replace the `TabsList` with a step indicator and Back/Next buttons. Keep the `Tabs` component for content switching (controlled via `value` prop), but replace the visible navigation:

```tsx
import { Check } from 'lucide-react';

// Helper for navigating questions
function navigateQuestion(direction: 'prev' | 'next') {
  const current = Number(activeTab);
  if (direction === 'next' && current < questions.length - 1) {
    setActiveTab(String(current + 1));
  } else if (direction === 'prev' && current > 0) {
    setActiveTab(String(current - 1));
  }
}

// In the render:
<Tabs value={activeTab} onValueChange={setActiveTab}>
  {/* Step indicator + Back/Next buttons (replaces TabsList) */}
  <div className="mb-2 flex items-center justify-between">
    <span className="text-muted-foreground text-xs">
      {questions[Number(activeTab)].header ?? `Question ${Number(activeTab) + 1} of ${questions.length}`}
    </span>
    <div className="flex items-center gap-1.5">
      <Button
        size="sm"
        variant="ghost"
        onClick={() => navigateQuestion('prev')}
        disabled={Number(activeTab) === 0}
        className="h-7 px-2 text-xs"
      >
        Back {isActive && <Kbd className="ml-1">&larr;</Kbd>}
      </Button>
      {Number(activeTab) < questions.length - 1 ? (
        <Button
          size="sm"
          onClick={() => navigateQuestion('next')}
          className="h-7 px-2 text-xs"
        >
          Next {isActive && <Kbd className="ml-1">&rarr;</Kbd>}
        </Button>
      ) : (
        <Button
          size="sm"
          onClick={handleSubmit}
          disabled={!isComplete() || submitting}
          className="h-7 px-2 text-xs"
        >
          <Check className="size-(--size-icon-xs)" /> Submit
          {isActive && <Kbd className="ml-1">Enter</Kbd>}
        </Button>
      )}
    </div>
  </div>

  {/* Content switching via hidden tab mechanism */}
  {questions.map((q, idx) => (
    <TabsContent key={idx} value={String(idx)} className="mt-0">
      {renderQuestionContent(q, idx)}
    </TabsContent>
  ))}
</Tabs>
```

Note: The `navigateQuestion` function may already exist in the imperative handle. Extract it as a local function for the buttons to use.

Also **remove the standalone Submit button** that currently appears below the Tabs component (around line 419), since the Submit button is now integrated into the Back/Next navigation bar on the last question.

## Keyboard Mapping

- Left arrow / `[` -> Back (existing `navigateQuestion('prev')` in useInteractiveShortcuts)
- Right arrow / `]` -> Next (existing `navigateQuestion('next')` in useInteractiveShortcuts)
- Enter -> Next question (or Submit on last) — handled by modified `submit()` in Task 3.3

